# Bug Solver Repositories

This file tells the bug analyzer which repositories to search when analyzing Jira issues.

Copy this file to `repositories.md` and update with your actual repository paths.

## /absolute/path/to/frontend-app
**Purpose:** Customer-facing web application
**Stack:** React, TypeScript, Next.js
**Covers:** UI bugs, authentication flows, checkout process, frontend routing
**Key areas:**
- src/components/ - React components
- src/api/ - API client code
- src/auth/ - Authentication logic
- src/pages/ - Next.js pages

## /absolute/path/to/backend-api
**Purpose:** REST API service
**Stack:** Python, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis
**Covers:** API endpoints, database operations, business logic, background jobs
**Key areas:**
- app/routes/ - API endpoints
- app/models/ - Database models
- app/services/ - Business logic layer
- app/tasks/ - Background tasks

## /absolute/path/to/mobile-app
**Purpose:** iOS and Android mobile application
**Stack:** React Native, TypeScript, Expo
**Covers:** Mobile-specific bugs, offline sync, push notifications, native features
**Key areas:**
- src/screens/ - App screens
- src/services/ - Background services
- src/hooks/ - React hooks
- src/native/ - Native modules
